statement.p:
 Let \(A = \left(
\begin{array}{cc}
 1 & 2 \\
 0 & -1 \\
\end{array}
\right)\), \(B= \left(
\begin{array}{ccc}
 3 & 7 & 6 \\
 2 & -1 & 5 \\
\end{array}
\right)\), and \(C= \left(
\begin{array}{ccc}
 0 & -2 & 4 \\
 7 & 1 & 1 \\
\end{array}
\right)\). Compute the following as efficiently as possible by using any of the Laws of Matrix Algebra:

li.p:
 \(AB+AC=\left(
\begin{array}{ccc}
 21 & 5 & 22 \\
 -9 & 0 & -6 \\
\end{array}
\right)\)

 \(A^{-1}=\left(
\begin{array}{cc}
 1 & 2 \\
 0 & -1 \\
\end{array}
\right)=A\)

